==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Laticlave
<hw>Lat"i*clave</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>laticlavus</ets>, <ets>laticlavium</ets>; <ets>latus</ets> broad +
<ets>clavus</ets> nail, a purple stripe on the tunica: cf. F.
<ets>laticlave</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Rom. Antiq.)</fld> <def>A broad
stripe of purple on the fore part of the tunic, worn by senators in
ancient Rome as an emblem of office.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

